{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867496907,"sessionID":"ses_2860cea5bffe2PuZNoGg4JayNy","part":{"id":"prt_d79f37d4d0018LHf3mIwOnx6js","messageID":"msg_d79f3710c001oiZ3MA2UXtNZot","sessionID":"ses_2860cea5bffe2PuZNoGg4JayNy","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2db1741933704444b5a7e3a5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n4: \n5: ## Package layout (every module path and role)\n6: \n7: | Path | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n10: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n11: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n12: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n13: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n14: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n15: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n16: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n17: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n18: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n19: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n20: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n21: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n22: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n23: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n24: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n25: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n26: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n27: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n28: \n29: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):  \n30: `agentcube`, `agentcube.cli`, `agentcube.runtime`, `agentcube.operations`, `agentcube.services`  \n31: *(Note: `agentcube.models` is not listed in `[tool.setuptools] packages` but is imported; packaging may rely on setuptools discovery for subpackages — reconstruct imports from source as above.)*\n32: \n33: ## Console script entry point\n34: \n35: ```toml\n36: [project.scripts]\n37: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Typer app object: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n41: \n42: ## Typer — root callback\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: def main(\n46:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n47:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n48:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n49:     ),\n50:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n51: ) -> None:\n52:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ## Typer — `pack`\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: def pack(\n59:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n60:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n61:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n62:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n63:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n64:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n65:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n66:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n67:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n68: ) -> None:\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Typer — `build`\n72: \n73: ```python\n74: def build(\n75:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n76:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n77:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n78:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n79:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n80: ) -> None:\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ## Typer — `publish`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def publish(\n87:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n88:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n89:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n90:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n91:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n92:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n93:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n94:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n95:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n96:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n97:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n98:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n99:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n100: ) -> None:\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ## Typer — `invoke`\n104: \n105: ```python\n106: def invoke(\n107:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n108:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n109:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n110:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n111:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n112: ) -> None:\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Typer — `status`\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: def status(\n119:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n120:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n121:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n122: ) -> None:\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ## Helper functions (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n126: \n127: ```python\n128: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None: ...\n129: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None: ...  # prints, typer.Exit(1)\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Runtime classes\n133: \n134: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: class PackRuntime:\n138:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n139:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n140:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n141:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n142:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n143:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n144:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n145:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n146:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n147:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n148:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n149:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n150:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n151:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n152:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n153:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n154:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### `BuildRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n158: \n159: ```python\n160: class BuildRuntime:\n161:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n162:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n163:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n164:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n165:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n166:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n167:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### `PublishRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: class PublishRuntime:\n174:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n175:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n176:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n177:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n178:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n179:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n180:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n181:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### `InvokeRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n185: \n186: ```python\n187: class InvokeRuntime:\n188:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n189:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n190:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n191:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n192:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n193: ```\n194: \n195: **Implementation note:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if the condition is false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError` (as of extracted source).\n196: \n197: ### `StatusRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: class StatusRuntime:\n201:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n202:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n203:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n204:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ## `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n208: \n209: ```python\n210: class DockerService:\n211:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n212:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n213:     def build_image(\n214:         self,\n215:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n216:         context_path: Path,\n217:         image_name: str,\n218:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n219:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n220:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n221:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n222:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n223:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n224:     def push_image(\n225:         self,\n226:         image_name: str,\n227:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n228:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n229:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n230:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n231:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n232:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n233:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ## `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n237: \n238: ```python\n239: class MetadataService:\n240:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n241:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n242:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n243:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n244:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n245:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n246:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n247: ```\n248: \n249: ## `KubernetesProvider` (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n250: \n251: ```python\n252: class KubernetesProvider:\n253:     def __init__(\n254:         self,\n255:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n256:         verbose: bool = False,\n257:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n258:     ) -> None: ...\n259:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n260:     def deploy_agent(\n261:         self,\n262:         agent_name: str,\n263:         image_url: str,\n264:         port: int,\n265:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n266:         replicas: int = 1,\n267:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n268:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n269:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n270:     def _create_deployment(\n271:         self,\n272:         name: str,\n273:         image_url: str,\n274:         port: int,\n275:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n276:         replicas: int,\n277:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n278:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n279:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n280:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n281:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n282:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n283:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ## `AgentCubeProvider` (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n287: \n288: ```python\n289: class AgentCubeProvider:\n290:     def __init__(\n291:         self,\n292:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n293:         verbose: bool = False,\n294:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n295:     ) -> None: ...\n296:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n297:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n298:         self,\n299:         agent_name: str,\n300:         image_url: str,\n301:         port: int,\n302:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n303:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n304:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n305:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n306:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n307:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n308:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n309:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n310:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n311: ```\n312: \n313: CR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n314: \n315: ## `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n316: \n317: | Field | Type | Default | `Field(..., description=...)` |\n318: |-------|------|---------|--------------------------------|\n319: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n320: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n321: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n322: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n323: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n324: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n325: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n326: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n327: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n328: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n329: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n330: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n331: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n332: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n333: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n334: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n335: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n336: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n337: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n338: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n339: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n340: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n341: \n342: Validators: `validate_language` → `['python','java']` lowercase; `validate_build_mode` → `['local','cloud']` lowercase; `validate_port` → `1..65535`.\n343: \n344: ## `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n345: \n346: Dataclass fields (all `Optional` unless noted):\n347: \n348: | Field | Type | Default |\n349: |-------|------|---------|\n350: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n351: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n352: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n353: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n354: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n355: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n356: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n357: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n358: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n359: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n360: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n361: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n362: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n363: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n364: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n365: \n366: ```python\n367: @classmethod\n368: def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\": ...\n369: ```\n370: \n371: ## Dependencies (`cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`)\n372: \n373: **`[project]` dependencies:**\n374: \n375: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0`\n376: - `pydantic>=2.0.0`\n377: - `pyyaml>=6.0`\n378: - `httpx>=0.24.0`\n379: - `docker>=6.0.0`\n380: - `rich>=13.0.0`\n381: - `packaging>=23.0`\n382: - `importlib-resources>=6.0.0`\n383: - `semver>=3.0.0`\n384: \n385: **Optional `[project.optional-dependencies]`:**\n386: \n387: - `k8s`: `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n388: - `dev`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `ruff>=0.1.0`, `mypy>=1.5.0`, `pre-commit>=3.3.0`, `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n389: - `test`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`, `httpx-mock>=0.10.0`\n390: \n391: **Python:** `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`.\n392: \n393: ## Top-level exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n394: \n395: - `__version__ = \"0.1.0\"`\n396: - `__author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"`\n397: - `__email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"`\n398: - Imports: `app`, `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`\n399: - `__all__` = `[\"app\", \"PackRuntime\", \"BuildRuntime\", \"PublishRuntime\", \"InvokeRuntime\"]`  \n400:   (`StatusRuntime` is not exported here.)\n\n(End of file - total 400 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n\n## Package layout (every module path and role)\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/cli-toolkit/design.md","time":{"start":1775867496883,"end":1775867496905}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867496914,"sessionID":"ses_2860cea5bffe2PuZNoGg4JayNy","part":{"id":"prt_d79f37f8d001CJZsK482jtTw6l","messageID":"msg_d79f3710c001oiZ3MA2UXtNZot","sessionID":"ses_2860cea5bffe2PuZNoGg4JayNy","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1845758fda084122b35f24f6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Main CLI module for AgentCube using Typer.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import json\n4: import logging\n5: import os\n6: import sys\n7: import traceback\n8: from pathlib import Path\n9: from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n10: \n11: import typer\n12: from rich.console import Console\n13: from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n14: \n15: from agentcube import __version__\n16: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n17: from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n18: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n19: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n20: from agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime\n21: \n22: app = typer.Typer(\n23:     name=\"agentcube\",\n24:     help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\",\n25:     no_args_is_help=True,\n26:     rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n27:     add_completion=False,\n28: )\n29: \n30: console = Console()\n31: \n32: \n33: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None:\n34:     \"\"\"Display version and exit.\"\"\"\n35:     if value:\n36:         console.print(f\"[bold green]AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}[/]\")\n37:         raise typer.Exit()\n38: \n39: \n40: @app.callback()\n41: def main(\n42:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n43:         None,\n44:         \"--version\",\n45:         help=\"Show version and exit\",\n46:         callback=version_callback,\n47:         is_eager=True,\n48:     ),\n49:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n50: ) -> None:\n51:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n52:     if verbose:\n53:         logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n54: \n55: \n56: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n57:     \"\"\"Handle errors consistently across commands.\"\"\"\n58:     console.print(f\"[bold red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/]\")\n59:     if verbose:\n60:         console.print(\"[bold red]Traceback:[/]\")\n61:         traceback.print_exc()\n62:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n63: \n64: \n65: @app.command()\n66: def pack(\n67:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n68:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n69:     ),\n70:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n71:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n72:         None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"\n73:     ),\n74:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n75:         None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"\n76:     ),\n77:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n78:         None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"\n79:     ),\n80:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n81:         None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"\n82:     ),\n83:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n84:         None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"\n85:     ),\n86:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n87:         None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"\n88:     ),\n89:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n90: ) -> None:\n91:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace by validating and preparing it.\"\"\"\n92:     try:\n93:         if verbose:\n94:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n95: \n96:         runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n97:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n98: \n99:         with Progress(\n100:             SpinnerColumn(),\n101:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n102:             console=console,\n103:         ) as progress:\n104:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n105: \n106:             options: Dict[str, Any] = {\n107:                 \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n108:                 \"language\": language,\n109:                 \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n110:                 \"port\": port,\n111:                 \"build_mode\": build_mode,\n112:                 \"description\": description,\n113:                 \"output\": output,\n114:             }\n115: \n116:             result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n117: \n118:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Packaging complete!\", completed=True)\n119: \n120:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Successfully packaged agent\")\n121:         console.print(f\"  Agent name: [cyan]{result['agent_name']}[/]\")\n122:         console.print(f\"  Workspace: [cyan]{result['workspace_path']}[/]\")\n123:         console.print(f\"  Metadata: [cyan]{result['metadata_path']}[/]\")\n124: \n125:     except Exception as e:\n126:         _handle_error(e, \"packaging agent\", verbose)\n127: \n128: \n129: @app.command()\n130: def build(\n131:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n132:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n133:     ),\n134:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n135:         None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"\n136:     ),\n137:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n138:         None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"\n139:     ),\n140:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n141:         None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"\n142:     ),\n143:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n144: ) -> None:\n145:     \"\"\"Build a container image from the packaged agent workspace.\"\"\"\n146:     try:\n147:         if verbose:\n148:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n149: \n150:         runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n151:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n152: \n153:         with Progress(\n154:             SpinnerColumn(),\n155:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n156:             console=console,\n157:         ) as progress:\n158:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Building image...\", total=None)\n159: \n160:             options: Dict[str, Any] = {\n161:                 \"proxy\": proxy,\n162:                 \"cloud_provider\": cloud_provider,\n163:                 \"output\": output,\n164:             }\n165: \n166:             result = runtime.build(workspace_path, **options)\n167: \n168:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Build complete!\", completed=True)\n169: \n170:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Successfully built image\")\n171:         console.print(f\"  Image name: [cyan]{result['image_name']}[/]\")\n172:         console.print(f\"  Image ID: [cyan]{result['image_id']}[/]\")\n173:         console.print(f\"  Image size: [cyan]{result['image_size']}[/]\")\n174: \n175:     except Exception as e:\n176:         _handle_error(e, \"building image\", verbose)\n177: \n178: \n179: @app.command()\n180: def publish(\n181:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n182:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n183:     ),\n184:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n185:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"\n186:     ),\n187:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n188:         None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"\n189:     ),\n190:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n191:         None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"\n192:     ),\n193:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n194:         None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"\n195:     ),\n196:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n197:         None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"\n198:     ),\n199:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n200:         None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"\n201:     ),\n202:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n203:         None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"\n204:     ),\n205:     provider: str = typer.Option(\n206:         \"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"\n207:     ),\n208:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n209:         None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"\n210:     ),\n211:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n212:         None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment\"\n213:     ),\n214:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n215:         None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"\n216:     ),\n217:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n218: ) -> None:\n219:     \"\"\"Publish an agent to the specified provider.\"\"\"\n220:     try:\n221:         if verbose:\n222:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n223: \n224:         runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n225:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n226: \n227:         with Progress(\n228:             SpinnerColumn(),\n229:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n230:             console=console,\n231:         ) as progress:\n232:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Publishing agent...\", total=None)\n233: \n234:             options: Dict[str, Any] = {\n235:                 \"version\": version,\n236:                 \"image_url\": image_url,\n237:                 \"image_username\": image_username,\n238:                 \"image_password\": image_password,\n239:                 \"description\": description,\n240:                 \"region\": region,\n241:                 \"cloud_provider\": cloud_provider,\n242:                 \"node_port\": node_port,\n243:                 \"replicas\": replicas,\n244:                 \"namespace\": namespace,\n245:             }\n246: \n247:             result = runtime.publish(workspace_path, **options)\n248: \n249:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Publish complete!\", completed=True)\n250: \n251:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Successfully published agent\")\n252:         console.print(f\"  Agent ID: [cyan]{result.get('agent_id', 'N/A')}[/]\")\n253:         console.print(f\"  Endpoint: [cyan]{result.get('endpoint', 'N/A')}[/]\")\n254: \n255:     except Exception as e:\n256:         _handle_error(e, \"publishing agent\", verbose)\n257: \n258: \n259: @app.command()\n260: def invoke(\n261:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n262:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n263:     ),\n264:     payload: str = typer.Option(\n265:         \"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"\n266:     ),\n267:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(\n268:         None,\n269:         \"--header\",\n270:         help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\",\n271:     ),\n272:     provider: str = typer.Option(\n273:         \"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"\n274:     ),\n275:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n276: ) -> None:\n277:     \"\"\"Invoke a published agent with the given payload.\"\"\"\n278:     try:\n279:         if verbose:\n280:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n281: \n282:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n283: \n284:         try:\n285:             payload_data: Dict[str, Any] = json.loads(payload)\n286:         except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n287:             console.print(f\"[bold red]Invalid JSON payload: {e}[/]\")\n288:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n289: \n290:         headers: Dict[str, str] = {}\n291:         if header_list:\n292:             for header in header_list:\n293:                 if \":\" not in header:\n294:                     console.print(f\"[bold red]Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value', got: {header}[/]\")\n295:                     raise typer.Exit(1)\n296:                 key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n297:                 headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n298: \n299:         runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n300: \n301:         with Progress(\n302:             SpinnerColumn(),\n303:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n304:             console=console,\n305:         ) as progress:\n306:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Invoking agent...\", total=None)\n307: \n308:             result = runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_data, headers)\n309: \n310:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Invoke complete!\", completed=True)\n311: \n312:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Successfully invoked agent\")\n313:         console.print(f\"  Response: [cyan]{json.dumps(result, indent=2)}[/]\")\n314: \n315:     except typer.Exit:\n316:         raise\n317:     except Exception as e:\n318:         _handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)\n319: \n320: \n321: @app.command()\n322: def status(\n323:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n324:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n325:     ),\n326:     provider: str = typer.Option(\n327:         \"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"\n328:     ),\n329:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n330: ) -> None:\n331:     \"\"\"Get the status of a published agent.\"\"\"\n332:     try:\n333:         if verbose:\n334:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n335: \n336:         runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n337:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n338: \n339:         with Progress(\n340:             SpinnerColumn(),\n341:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n342:             console=console,\n343:         ) as progress:\n344:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Getting status...\", total=None)\n345: \n346:             result = runtime.get_status(workspace_path, provider)\n347: \n348:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Status retrieved!\", completed=True)\n349: \n350:         if result[\"status\"] in (\"not_published\", \"error\"):\n351:             console.print(f\"[bold red]✗[/] Agent status: {result['status']}[/]\")\n352:             if result[\"status\"] == \"not_published\":\n353:                 console.print(\"  Please publish the agent first using 'agentcube publish'\")\n354:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n355: \n356:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Agent status: {result['status']}[/]\")\n357:         for key, value in result.items():\n358:             if key != \"status\":\n359:                 console.print(f\"  {key}: [cyan]{value}[/]\")\n360: \n361:     except typer.Exit:\n362:         raise\n363:     except Exception as e:\n364:         _handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)\n365: \n366: \n367: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n368:     app()\n\n(End of file - total 368 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Main CLI module for AgentCube using Typer.\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport logging\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport traceback\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n\nimport typer\nfrom rich.console import Console\nfrom rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n\nfrom agentcube import __version__\nfrom agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py","time":{"start":1775867496885,"end":1775867496912}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867496917,"sessionID":"ses_2860cea5bffe2PuZNoGg4JayNy","part":{"id":"prt_d79f3849d001XnDNn0Pn6V0VSe","messageID":"msg_d79f3710c001oiZ3MA2UXtNZot","sessionID":"ses_2860cea5bffe2PuZNoGg4JayNy","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c8e668d12ef644aea2bc12ff","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Runtime for the build command.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import logging\n4: import re\n5: from pathlib import Path\n6: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n7: \n8: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n9: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n10: \n11: \n12: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n13: \n14: \n15: class BuildRuntime:\n16:     \"\"\"Runtime for building agent images.\"\"\"\n17: \n18:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n19:         \"\"\"Initialize the build runtime.\"\"\"\n20:         self.verbose = verbose\n21:         if verbose:\n22:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n23:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n24:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n25: \n26:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n27:         \"\"\"Build a Docker image for the agent.\"\"\"\n28:         logger.info(f\"Building workspace: {workspace_path}\")\n29: \n30:         metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n31:         \n32:         original_version = metadata.version\n33:         self._increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)\n34:         \n35:         self._validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path, metadata.build_mode)\n36: \n37:         try:\n38:             if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n39:                 result = self._build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n40:             else:\n41:                 result = self._build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n42: \n43:             self._update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, result)\n44:             return result\n45: \n46:         except Exception as e:\n47:             if original_version != metadata.version:\n48:                 logger.warning(f\"Build failed, reverting version from {metadata.version} to {original_version}\")\n49:                 metadata.version = original_version\n50:                 self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n51:             raise\n52: \n53:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n54:         \"\"\"Increment the version for the build.\"\"\"\n55:         if metadata.version:\n56:             version_parts = re.match(r\"(\\d+)\\.(\\d+)\\.(\\d+)(?:-(.+))?\", metadata.version)\n57:             if version_parts:\n58:                 major = int(version_parts.group(1))\n59:                 minor = int(version_parts.group(2))\n60:                 patch = int(version_parts.group(3))\n61:                 prerelease = version_parts.group(4)\n62: \n63:                 if prerelease:\n64:                     prerelease_parts = re.match(r\"(\\d+)(?:\\.(.+))?\", prerelease)\n65:                     if prerelease_parts:\n66:                         build_num = int(prerelease_parts.group(1)) + 1\n67:                         suffix = prerelease_parts.group(2) or \"\"\n68:                         if suffix:\n69:                             metadata.version = f\"{major}.{minor}.{patch}-{build_num}.{suffix}\"\n70:                         else:\n71:                             metadata.version = f\"{major}.{minor}.{patch}-{build_num}\"\n72:                     else:\n73:                         metadata.version = f\"{major}.{minor}.{patch}-{prerelease}.1\"\n74:                 else:\n75:                     patch += 1\n76:                     metadata.version = f\"{major}.{minor}.{patch}\"\n77:             else:\n78:                 metadata.version = f\"{metadata.version}-1\"\n79:         else:\n80:             metadata.version = \"0.1.0\"\n81: \n82:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n83:         logger.info(f\"Incremented version to: {metadata.version}\")\n84:         return metadata.version\n85: \n86:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path, build_mode: str = \"local\") -> None:\n87:         \"\"\"Validate that build prerequisites are met.\"\"\"\n88:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n89:         if not dockerfile_path.exists():\n90:             raise ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace. Run 'pack' first.\")\n91: \n92:         if build_mode == \"local\" and not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n93:             raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n94: \n95:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n96:         \"\"\"Build the image locally using Docker.\"\"\"\n97:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n98:         image_name = f\"{metadata.agent_name}:{metadata.version or 'latest'}\"\n99: \n100:         build_args: Dict[str, str] = {}\n101:         proxy = options.get(\"proxy\")\n102:         if proxy:\n103:             build_args[\"HTTP_PROXY\"] = proxy\n104:             build_args[\"HTTPS_PROXY\"] = proxy\n105: \n106:         result = self.docker_service.build_image(\n107:             dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n108:             context_path=workspace_path,\n109:             image_name=metadata.agent_name,\n110:             tag=metadata.version or \"latest\",\n111:             build_args=build_args if build_args else None,\n112:         )\n113: \n114:         result[\"image_name\"] = image_name\n115:         return result\n116: \n117:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n118:         \"\"\"Build the image in the cloud.\"\"\"\n119:         cloud_provider = options.get(\"cloud_provider\", \"huawei\")\n120: \n121:         logger.info(f\"Building in cloud with provider: {cloud_provider}\")\n122: \n123:         return {\n124:             \"image_name\": f\"{cloud_provider}/{metadata.agent_name}:{metadata.version or 'latest'}\",\n125:             \"image_id\": \"cloud-build-id\",\n126:             \"image_size\": \"Unknown\",\n127:             \"build_time\": \"cloud-build-time\",\n128:         }\n129: \n130:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None:\n131:         \"\"\"Update metadata with build information.\"\"\"\n132:         metadata.image = metadata.image or {}\n133:         metadata.image.update(build_result)\n134: \n135:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n(End of file - total 135 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Runtime for the build command.\"\"\"\n\nimport logging\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\nfrom agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass BuildRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime for building agent images.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize the build runtime.\"\"\"\n        self.verbose = verbose","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py","time":{"start":177586